negotiations have included, at a minimum, submittal of a written conditional offer or a letter of intent and counter offer or counter letter of intent).  If Landlord fails to notify Tenant in writing of such election within such period, Landlord shall be deemed to have waived option (ii) above, but written approval by Landlord of the proposed assignee or sublessee shall still be required.  Failure by Landlord to approve a proposed subtenant or assignee shall not cause a termination of this Lease.
 
