ARTICLE 19. TERMINATION RIGHTS
 
.  Tenant shall have the one-time right (the " ") to terminate this Lease as to the entire Premises then leased hereunder or as to one or more Deletion Increments (as defined below), effective as of the end of the Seventh Rent Year (the ""), by giving Landlord not less than twelve (12) months prior written notice of such termination (the "").  The Termination Notice shall be irrevocable and shall specify whether the Termination Option is being exercised (i) with respect to the entire Premises then leased hereunder or (ii) with respect to one or more Deletion Increments, in which event the Termination Notice shall specifically describe the Deletion Increments to be terminated hereunder.   For the purposes of this Article 19, a " " is, with respect to each floor on which a portion of the Premises is located as of the Early Termination Right, the entire Premises located on such floor.  If the Termination Notice fails to specify whether it is applicable to the entire Premises or to one or more Deletion Increments, it shall be deemed to apply to the entire Premises.  That portion of the Premises described in the Termination Notice is referred to herein as the " ."
