e.  Any delay in Substantial Completion (as defined below) of the Tenant Improvements resulting from any revision to the Final Plans or the budget shall constitute a Tenant Delay as defined in and subject to Section 11 below.  If Tenant fails to raise any objections to the analysis and/or budget within the period(s) described above, Tenant shall be deemed to have approved Landlord's Contractor's recommended bid acceptance and proposed budget.  Upon approval of the estimated budget and selection of the subcontractors, Landlord's Contractor shall provide Tenant with Landlord's Contractor's reasonable and good faith estimate of the date by which it anticipates the Tenant Improvements will be completed (the "").
