39.01
                   
Notwithstanding any other provisions of this Lease to the contrary, Tenant shall have the one-time right to cancel and terminate this Lease with respect to the entire Premises only, effective as of the day (the "") preceding the tenth (10
Cancellation Date
th
) anniversary of the Rent Commencement Date, provided that each of the following conditions is satisfied:  (i) Tenant shall give Landlord not less than eighteen (18) months prior written notice of its election to cancel and terminate this Lease (""), (ii) there shall not be any default beyond any applicable notice and cure period under this Lease at the time Tenant's Notice of Cancellation is given, and there shall not be any default beyond any applicable notice and cure period in the payment of any Rent or in Tenant's obligation to remove any specialty alterations that Tenant is required to have removed on the Cancellation Date; (iii) Tenant shall have paid to Landlord at the time of the giving of Tenant's Notice of Cancellation an amount equal to the straight-line unamortized portion of (a) the Landlord's Contribution actually disbursed to Tenant; (b) the brokerage commissions and legal fees incurred
